  "description": [
    "18 COUNTY MERGERS OFFER TAX SAVINGS FOR VIRGINIANS AGED SYSTEM IS BURDENSOME TO CITIZENS Legislature Has Chance to End Clumsy Wasteful Governmental Plan By JOHN E TAYLOR Virginias legislators who will Convene next month have before them an opportunity to celebrate the tercentenary of the founding of the eight original shires or counties of the State by legis lating out of existence the ar chaic cumbersome and wasteful form of county government that Is today practically the same as it was 300 years ago The legislators could relieve the burden of the taxpayers by en acting legislation consolidating a number of the 100 counties bring ing the total of counties in the State to about 50 Such a move would eliminate hundreds of job holders do away with the cost of maintaining court houses jails and other institu tions in many of the counties Huge Savings Possible It is hard to estimate in dollars and cents just how much this would save but it is a foregone conclusion the savings would be enormous For the last few years the 100 counties have been spending about 528000000 a year and this figure does not include the fees and com missions paid"
  ],
